title.narrative: 1.2 Ministry of Health and Sanitation has increased capacity to deliver quality MNCAH+N services, including in emergencies.

description.narrative: Seven additional Special Care Baby Units were established covering 14 out of 16 districts. A cumulative total of 2.2 million children benefited from polio and routine vaccination campaigns. Improvement of cold chain system and vaccine stock management practices with introduction of an online tool has enabled readiness for scaling-up COVID-19 vaccination while maintaining childhood immunization. With UNICEF-procured Integrated Management of Acute Malnutrition (IMAM) supplies, 34,387 severely acute malnourished children were cured. Following the campaign, semester-1 Vitamin A supplementation coverage improved to 98 percent. Milestone policy documents were launched on elimination of mother-to-child HIV transmission (EMTCT) and equipment maintenance and management.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
